New Records: Giannis Antetokounmpo passed Kareem Abdul-Jabbar for the most double-doubles in Bucks history with his 432nd double-double
Key Match Events: The Bucks won 121-105 against the San Antonio Spurs
Giannis Antetokounmpo had a double-double with 25 points, 16 rebounds, and 8 assists
Post-Match Reflections: The Bucks have scratched and clawed all the way out of their hole and climbed back into the playoff picture
Coach Doc Rivers and company are one of the most talented in the NBA, but one of the oldest teams in the league
Miscellaneous Highlights: Giannis Antetokounmpo is averaging 31.6 points, 11.6 rebounds, and 6.1 assists per game
Damian Lillard is starting to find his groove alongside Antetokounmpo
Khris Middleton has returned from double ankle surgery and is back in the swing of things
Others: The Bucks are above the play-in threshold in the Eastern Conference
